    TAP BROTHERS

    Our Story:
    From Brazil,
    With Heart

    TAP began with a simple idea from Roberto Simonsen: to share Brazil’s most nostalgic foods Tapioca, Açaí, and Pão de Queijo with the world. What started as a local vision quickly evolved into a fast-casual wellness brand that redefines convenience without compromising on culture or quality.

    We source real ingredients, craft every dish with care, and do it all with a rhythm that’s unmistakably Brazilian.

    From New York to Miami and beyond, TAP is becoming a lifestyle destination for locals, tourists, health-seekers, and homesick Brazilians alike.

    “We’re not just serving food—we’re sharing Brazil. Every bowl, every bite, every smile at TAP is part of a bigger story: one of culture, connection, and creativity. Come feel the rhythm.”  Pedro Uchoa (CEO & Brand Visionary)

    “Our mission is simple: make people feel good—every day, every store, every moment. TAP is where comfort meets care, and where Brazilian hospitality wraps around you like home.”  Cleo Uchoa (COO & Operations Soul)

    WHY GLUTEN-FREE?

    We realized that the three best things in the world (tapioca, açaí, and pão de queijo) are naturally gluten-free. So why include gluten at all?

    That’s why every TAP location is completely gluten-free and safe from cross-contamination. Our menu is delicious, balanced, and 100% gluten-free! Crafted to fuel your day from morning to night with variety and flavor for every moment.
